## Module Structure
```
src/module_name/
├── __init__.py          # Exports all public interfaces
├── base.py              # Abstract base classes
├── types.py             # Module-specific types (if needed)
├── factory.py           # Factory classes
├── implementation.py    # Concrete implementations
└── utils.py            # Module-specific utilities
```

### Import Organization in __init__.py
```python
# Base classes first
from .base import BaseClass, AbstractInterface

# Main implementations
from .implementation import ConcreteClass1, ConcreteClass2

# Factory and utilities
from .factory import ComponentFactory
from .utils import utility_function

# Type definitions
from .types import CustomType

__all__ = [
    # Base classes
    'BaseClass', 'AbstractInterface',
    
    # Implementations  
    'ConcreteClass1', 'ConcreteClass2',
    
    # Factory
    'ComponentFactory',
    
    # Utilities
    'utility_function',
    
    # Types
    'CustomType',
]
```